THE MAN WITH A VISION

BASIC INFORMATION ABOUT THE ORIGIN OF THE MINISTRY

In the year 1989, "A burden was laid by the Lord in my heart for the young people". The burden had become heavier as i see the addiction of drugs, alcoholism, misery caused to parents and the spiritual need of the young people. Through fervent prayer a vision was given to reach out to young people, particularly in the North Eastern region of India with a message of Salvation through Christ. However, it took 18 years to establish Youth Harvest Ministry on 18th August 2009, as an independent faith based ministry.

God the Holy Spirit has inspired the name of the ministry as YOUTH HARVEST MINISTRY based on the promised word of God, John 4: 35-36 "...see how they are already white for the Harvest…, for he is gathering fruit unto eternal life".  The voice was clear from the Lord, as me and my wife were fasting and waiting on the Lord, "Disciple my Children, whom I harvest them. Teach them to follow me, equip them to witness me and to live an overcoming, abundant life". 

Since the voice continued to speak into my heart for the last four years, with much prayer and assurance from the Lord, harvest LEADERSHIP and DISCIPLESHIP TRAINING INSTITUTE was born under the umbrella of Youth Harvest Ministry.

As the name clearly suggest, it will help, train and equip young people to live life to the fullness and to continue walking with the Lord without backsliding.

BASIC INFORMATION ABOUT YHM

Youth Harvest Ministry is registered under the Government of Nagaland, Gov/Reg.No 6177. This ministry came into existence in the year 2009, according to God's Vision through a humble servant of God Rev. Kilang Jamir.

Under the divine direction Youth Harvest Ministry runs Harvest Leadership & Discipleship Training Institute (HLDTI), which trains and equips believers to walk victoriously and witness Christ effectively.

WHAT IS HARVEST LEADERSHIP & DISCIPLESHIP TRAINING INSTITUTE?

Harvest Leadership & Discipleship Training Institute is an intensive One Year Diploma course. Every subject taught in the institution is thoroughly furnished Biblically. Examination is conducted at the completion of every subject.

Every year training session begins from 8th February and completes the course in the 2nd week of December. At the completion of the course, students are honoured with a certificate and a mark sheet during the graduation programme.

ACTIVITIES 
Harvest Leadership & Discipleship Training Institute is backed with lot of activities which boost individual learning besides their class learning. Activities include both physical and mental involvement such as: 

Morning Devotion: Our first activity begins with the morning devotion, meditating and reading the word of God. This brings more insights of the word of God to an individual. Hence also brings spiritual growth.
Social work: Light works are done every day so that the students learn the importance of work and dignity of labor.
Leading Praise and Worship: Students are divided into different groups and they practically involved in learning songs and later they are allowed to lead the worship when they are equipped. This is one activity which also helps a person to discover their gifts and talents and to use it for the glory of God.
Games and Sports: The students are encouraged to participate in games and sports as they learn the importance of team work and promote mental & spiritual well-being.
Evening & Sunday worship: This is one of the most important aspects of our activities, where at the close of the day and Sunday we come together and worship in the spirit. Restoring and feeding our spiritual life with the word of God.
Children Ministry: Every Sunday Morning, staff and students minister to the Children who comes from different background and communities.
Practical Outreach Ministry: Staff and Students often go out as a team for Church Revival meetings and other practical field Ministry.

PURPOSE

To lead young people to Christ for personal Salvation.
To Disciple believers, to be victorious overcomers in every aspect of their lives.
To equip and assist young people for evangelism.
To inculcate in individual an ever deepener hunger to know Christ through the study of the word of God and corporate worship.
To equip the young people to be an instrument in bringing about a revival in the Church and in society.

ADDRESS AND CONTACT 

YOUTH HARVEST MINISTRY, Shekina    cove, Naga United Village, 4th Mile.
Dimapur, 797115,Nagaland.
Contact : +91 9862 4835 57,9089354113




