About Gitimbine United Methodist Church

Welcome to Gitimbine United Methodist Church,a vibrant and growing congregation rooted in Meru Town, Kenya. Since our establishment in 2008, we have been dedicated to spreading the love of Christ, nurturing spiritual growth, and serving our community with compassion and faith.

Our Heritage and Affiliation 
Gitimbine UMC falls under the Mount Kenya District within the Kenya-Ethiopia Annual Conference of the Methodist Church. Our church is committed to living out the Christian faith through worship, fellowship, service, and outreach initiatives that transform lives and communities.

Our Ministries 
We believe in holistic ministry that addresses spiritual, social, and community needs. To this end, we have established specialized ministries:

- Deaf Ministry: Focused on serving members who are deaf or hard-of-hearing, ensuring they experience God's love and participate fully in church life.  
- Youth Ministry: Dedicated to empowering young people through faith-based programs, mentorship, leadership training, and community engagement, nurturing the next generation of Christian leaders.

Educational and Training Programs 
To equip believers for effective service and leadership, we established the UMC Meru School of Theological Studies. This Bible school offers comprehensive theological education and spiritual formation, preparing students for ministry and leadership roles.

In partnership with Breakthrough International Bible University, we currently offer diploma and degree programs in theology. These academic programs aim to deepen biblical understanding and enhance practical ministry skills among our students, fostering a well-equipped church workforce committed to service.

Our Mission  
“To nurture and develop a Christ-centered community that promotes spiritual growth, inclusivity, and service, equipping believers to impact their communities with the love of Christ.”

Our Vision 
“To be a vibrant, inclusive, and transformative church that champions faith, empowerment, and social renewal within Meru Town and beyond, inspiring lives to be changed through the Gospel.”

Core Values
- Faith and Worship  
- Community and Fellowship  
- Service and Outreach  
- Education and Growth  
- Inclusivity and Diversity

Our Commitment 
At Gitimbine UMC, we are committed to creating an environment where everyone feels welcomed, valued, and empowered to grow in faith and serve others. Whether you are new to faith or seeking a spiritual home, you will find a supportive community ready to walk alongside you.

Contact Us 
We would love to hear from you! Feel free to reach out through the following contact details:

- Phone: 0723 659 555 / 0756 817 001  
- Email: umcgitimbine@gmail.com

Come and join us as we worship, learn, and serve together. We look forward to welcoming you to our church family!